{
  "stem": "27748.5",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we agreed while we were getting acquainted to at least spend some time, but it might be a good idea to emigrate to Israel altogether.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And this is eventually what we did.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That is, we first spent one year in Israel, kind of a sabbatical for me, and during which time we arranged for me to get a professor job at the University of Tel Aviv, in-- starting in 1972.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So then we went back-- we were in Israel from '69 to '70, I believe it was, went back for one year to Buffalo, and then sort of wound up my affairs and went to-- emigrated to Israel.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "What happened in Israel was pretty much of a shock in my life.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Israel has a very sophisticated program for teaching people the Hebrew language.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It's called Ulpan.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It's sort of a total immersion program.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "That is, you live in a setting where you're given housing and food.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And if you have children, you get child support-- child care.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "All you have to do is learn the language.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And for most people, this works very well, for most of the immigrants.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "The Israelis had lots of experience at teaching people Hebrew and they've worked this out to a fine art.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Well, what worked for most people didn't work for me.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "During the three months or so that we spent in this absorption center during the class, I never spoke.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I never opened my mouth.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I simply froze and I didn't learn Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, what I learned much later-- several-- about 10 years later was that there have been studies of children who were taken from one country to another and had to learn a new language, one they didn't know before, and were in new settings.",
      "word_count": 44
    }
  ],
